parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to not retract properly, leading to loose or unsecured seat belts, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: the seat belt does not retract
the seat belt buckle is broken
the red release button is broken
the seat belt is difficult to latch or unlatch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to not latch or unlatch properly, leading to loose or unsecured seat belts, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle is broken
the red release button is broken
the seat belt is difficult to latch or unlatch
the seat belt buckle will not lock into the harness.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships to properly repair recalled seat belts can lead to continued safety risks for vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Dealerships refuse to repair recalled seat belts
dealerships claim that the recall is not applicable to the vehicle
dealerships do not have the necessary parts to complete the repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracking or failure of the frame rail can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to loss of steering control, unusual noises, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Clicking and popping noises when turning the wheel
knocking sounds when trying to steer
hood falls down when lifting due to failed hydraulic strut rods/pistons.
